Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
timing_defer_m...object_updates(25.10)  timing_defer_m...object_updates(25.10)

Name
       timing_defer_mmmc_object_updates

Syntax
       timing_defer_mmmc_object_updates

       {true | false}

       Default: false

       Allows  a sequence of MMMC updates to be accumulated before new data is
       loaded and analyzed.

       When set to false, the multi-mode multi-corner (MMMC) update  commands,
       update_constraint_mode and update_analysis_view, actively load new data
       upon  execution. Since all the timing information is reloaded with each
       update command, executing a sequence of updates can result in  multiple
       reloads  and  a  subsequent degradation of performance and turn-around-
       time.

       If the set_analysis_view -update_timing  parameter  is  specified,  the
       software  indicates  that  the MMMC object updates are complete and new
       configuration can be loaded and analyzed.

       For example:

       tempus >  update_constraint_mode  -name  ioTiming  -sdc_files  {postCt-
       sIO.sdc}

       tempus    >    update_constraint_mode   -name   coreTiming   -sdc_files
       {postCtsCore.sdc}

       tempus > set_analysis_view -update_timing

       For example:

       update_constraint_mode -name ioTiming -sdc_files {postCtsIO.sdc}

       update_constraint_mode -name coreTiming -sdc_files {postCtsCore.sdc}

       set_analysis_view -update_timing

       To set this global variable, use the set command.

